## About

I work at Ambee, a climate intelligence company focused on transforming environmental data into actionable insights for businesses, healthcare systems, and operational decision-making.

My work sits at the intersection of product marketing, climate intelligence, research communication, and strategic storytelling. I enjoy translating complex scientific systems into narratives people can actually understand and act on.

I’m particularly interested in how environmental signals influence human systems: health, cities, mobility, insurance, healthcare infrastructure, and everyday behavior.

Beyond marketing, I spend a lot of time studying communication psychology, internet culture, digital behavior, and how modern attention shapes perception.

